<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 937 POUNDS OF COCAINE SEIZED IN RAID; 2 
HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police have seized 937 pounds of cocaine worth $142 million in a bust in which 
two suspects were arrested, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The seizure followed months of surveillance and culminated Saturday in the 
parking lot of a Rosemead restaurant, where the drugs were found in a vehicle, 
Lt. Frank Pagueros said. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested were Benito de la Cruz, 37, and Daniel Chacon, 35, both Mexican 
nationals who were being held on $5-million bail. Narcotics detectives said the 
operation was not yet complete and declined to release further details. 
</P>
<P>
The seizure was the largest in the area since February, when FBI agents 
recovered 4,716 pounds in Fullerton. 
</P>
