<TEXT>
<P>
K mart Corp.: The Troy, Mich.-based retailer said first-quarter profit rose to 
$100.1 million, a 6.4% increase over the same period in 1989, while sales rose 
16.1% to $7.04 billion. 
</P>
<P>
Sales on a comparable store basis -- those stores open at least one year -- 
were up 6.2%. However, interest expense rose 70.2% due to larger short-term 
borrowings, and gross margin dipped from 27.9% to 26% reflecting lower shelf 
prices. The company said profit improvements resulted from increased sales, 
cost controls and favorable weather conditions for sales of seasonal 
merchandise. 
</P>
