<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS: OLSON INDUSTRIES POSTS FIRST-QUARTER PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Olson Industries Inc., continuing a financial rebound, reported a first-quarter 
profit of $595,658 compared with a year-earlier loss of $663,025. 
</P>
<P>
Olson's only operating unit is Dolco Packaging, a maker of plastic packaging 
products now reorganizing under Chapter 11 of the federal bankruptcy laws. In 
the past two quarters, the Sherman Oaks-based company has reported profits 
after suffering heavy losses earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The profit in the latest quarter, which ended March 31, came despite a slight 
drop in sales, to $18.9 million from $19.1 million. Olson attributed the 
earnings to a 16% decline in its average price for resin, the key raw material 
used in its packaging products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
