<P>
TEACHER ARRESTED IN KILLING AT SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A science teacher was preparing to blow up Hickman County High School in 
Centerville, Tenn., when the assistant principal discovered him, so he shot the 
administrator to death, the Nashville Banner, quoting unidentified 
investigators, reported. 
</P>
<P>
Teacher Donald Givens is charged with fatally shooting Assistant Principal Ron 
Wallace, then setting fire to the school, authorities said. Givens was being 
held without bond at the county jail. Supt. Wayne Qualls said several student 
complaints had been lodged against Givens, 50, and the teacher may have feared 
he was about to lose his tenured job. 
</P>
</TEXT>
