<P>
The number of Oakland voters who have little or no interest in bringing the 
Raiders back from Los Angeles has increased slightly, to 63%, according to an 
Oakland Tribune-Gallup Poll. 
</P>
<P>
Last February, the total was 59%. 
</P>
<P>
In the latest poll, 46% of the respondents considered it "not at all important" 
to complete a new deal to bring back the Raiders, and 17% said it was "not too 
important," 14% said it was "very important" and 20% said it was "somewhat 
important." Only 3% had no opinion. 
