<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: AZTECS OPEN AGAINST MIDDLE TENNESSEE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT MILLER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Having won the Western Athletic Conference championship Saturday in Hawaii, the 
San Diego State baseball team learned Monday it will open NCAA tournament play 
at 9 a.m. Thursday against Middle Tennessee State (42-13) in the West I 
Regional at Stanford University. 
</P>
<P>
The Aztecs (46-20), winners of 13 consecutive games, are seeded third. 
</P>
<P>
Middle Tennessee State, champion of the Ohio Valley Conference, is seeded 
fourth. 
</P>
<P>
"I was happy to see us seeded third," SDSU baseball coach Jim Dietz said. 
"We'll be the home team over (three) teams no matter what happens. Only two 
schools will be home over us, and that's an advantage in a six-team 
double-elimination tournament. That says a lot for this team." 
</P>
<P>
Dietz and his assistants will be scrambling to put together a scouting report 
on Middle Tennessee State. 
</P>
<P>
"I just know they're from Tennessee, and I know they went 14-0 in their 
conference," he said. "I imagine they'll be a very good team." 
</P>
<P>
Other first-round games in the West I Regional Thursday: second-seeded Southern 
Illinois (47-12) vs. fifth-seeded Fresno State (37-22) and top-seeded Stanford 
(52-10) vs. sixth-seeded Campbell (15-31). 
</P>
<P>
If the Aztecs win Thursday, they will play the Stanford-Campbell loser at 12:30 
p.m. Friday. If the Aztecs lose Thursday, they will play the Southern 
Illinois-Fresno State loser at 9 a.m. Friday. 
</P>
<P>
TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma Nazarene College's Shannon Anderson advanced to the third round of 
the NAIA women's championships with a 7-5, 6-4 victory over Kelly Nawroth of 
Baker College (Kan.). Kim Wright and Dion Shillito of PLNC won their first 
round matches but lost in the second round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
