<TEXT>
<P>
Yeutter Criticizes Japanese Minister: Secretary Clayton K. Yeutter blasted his 
Japanese counterpart Tomio Yamamoto for reportedly saying the United States had 
interfered in Japan's internal affairs by suggesting it liberalize its 
protected rice market. "I am very troubled by these comments, " he said in a 
letter to the Japanese agriculture minister that was made public. 
</P>
<P>
Yeutter also sought a meeting with the Japanese official to discuss the issue 
further and suggested that it be held during a ministerial meeting of the 
Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development in Paris next week. He 
said Yamamoto was quoted last week in a newspaper as having said Japan would 
not tolerate further meddling by U.S. officials in its rice policy. Japan 
virtually bans imports of rice to protect its farmers from lower-priced 
imports. 
</P>
