<P>
350,000 MARCH IN FAROOQ RITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SRINAGAR, India 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 350,000 mourners beating their breasts and crying for revenge marched 
today in a funeral procession for the chief Muslim cleric of Kashmir, who was 
assassinated in his home by three unknown gunmen. 
</P>
<P>
The procession passed peacefully although police say at least 50 died Monday 
when security forces fired on thousands of Muslims who seized Mirwaiz Maulvi 
Farooq's body from a hospital and carried it through the streets. 
</P>
<P>
Police reported 25 of the 50 victims had died in hospitals after shootings 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Police took no chances at the funeral, deploying thousands of combat-ready 
troops across the tense summer capital of Jammu and Kashmir state. The 
predominantly Muslim Kashmir area has been convulsed since mid-January by an 
uprising against Indian rule. 
</P>
<P>
A curfew was lifted in the areas through which the 3-mile-long funeral 
procession passed today and authorities withdrew security forces from those 
areas to avoid provocations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
