</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MINNEAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dayton Hudson Corp. today reported earnings of $58 million or 70 cents a share 
for the first quarter ended May 5, 1990, up 37% from $40 million or 51 cents a 
share during the corresponding period last year. 
</P>
<P>
Revenues for the quarter were $3.01 billion. Total revenues for the 
corporation's three operating companies increased 13% from the same period in 
1989, while comparable store revenues rose 7%. 
</P>
<P>
All three of the corporation's operating companies -- Target, Mervyn's and 
Dayton Hudson Department Store -- reported increased comparable-store revenues. 
</P>
