</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The May 12 presentation of Comic Relief '90 on HBO has now generated a record 
$8.6 million in funds, it was announced today by Bob Zmuda, president of the 
Comic Relief organization. As of Monday, pledges for the fourth all-star event 
to benefit America's homeless were running $2 million higher than at the same 
point last year. 
</P>
<P>
The $8.6-million tally includes: $6.9 million in pledges; $700,000 in ticket 
sales for the live presentation at Radio City Music Hall; $500,000 from 
corporate sponsor Canada Dry; $400,000 raised at local events across the 
country, and $100,000 taken in from merchandising and special events conducted 
in New York City the week before the live show. A total of 175,000 people have 
phoned in pledges, averaging $45 per pledge. 
</P>
