<P>
'NEWHART' WIFE TURNS SEDUCTRESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actress Mary Frann, the sweater-clad TV wife on CBS-TV's "Newhart," moves from 
innkeeper to vamp in the six-hour NBC-TV miniseries based on Jackie Collins' 
best seller "Lucky." 
</P>
<P>
After seven years of playing Bob Newhart's wife, Joanna Loudon, on "Newhart," 
Frann transforms herself into a seductive senator's wife who introduces a 
gangster to the joy of sex. 
</P>
<P>
"In 'Newhart' I wore sweaters. In 'Lucky' I vamp around in lingerie. I just 
hope the set is warm," Frann said Monday, hours before the final "Newhart" 
episode aired. 
</P>
<P>
"Lucky" is currently in development. 
