</P>
<P>
GRAF, SELES TOP FRENCH SEEDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two-time champion Steffi Graf and Monica Seles, who ended Graf's 66-match 
winning streak last Sunday, will be the top two seeds at the French Open tennis 
tournament, according to the Women's International Tennis Assn. rankings. 
</P>
<P>
Although there may be late withdrawals until Friday, when the final seeding 
list becomes official, today's seedings follow the WITA rankings among the 
players entered. 
</P>
<P>
The $5.35-million event, the second leg of the Grand Slam, is to begin Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Graf, who won the French Open in 1987 and 1988, is the top seed according to 
her No. 1 world ranking. She also was victorious in the Australian Open in 
January, the first Grand Slam event of the year. 
</P>
<P>
Martina Navratilova, ranked second in the world, is skipping the premier 
clay-court tournament. Instead, she is focusing on grass court play in 
preparation for Wimbledon, which begins next month. 
</P>
